learning_outcomes.en:
Upon completing the MA thesis the student:
- establishes research questions independently and select suitable theoretical treatments and methods for their analysis;
- structures research logically and purposefully;
- independently finds and uses suitable empirical and theoretical sources;
- argues and justifies their standpoints understandably and logically;
- uses terms, data and facts correctly and knows the rules of formalising research work;
- bases their conclusions on analysis and summarises in conformity with the line of thought of the thesis; and
- can explain and defend the results of their research in academic discussion and answer questions related to the research.

learning_outcomes.et:
Magistritöö kaitsnud üliõpilane:
- püstitab uurimisküsimusi ning valib nende uurimiseks sobivaid teoreetilisi käsitlusi ja metoodikaid;
- struktureerib tööd loogiliselt ja otstarbekalt;
- kasutab korrektseid termineid, andmeid ja fakte ning tunneb uurimistöö vormistuse reegleid;
- argumenteerib ning põhjendab oma seisukohti arusaadavalt ja loogiliseltning, toetab neid sobivate allikatega;
- kasutab arvandmeid ning neid tõlgendab;
- tugineb oma järeldustes analüüsile ning teeb kokkuvõtteid, mis on kooskõlas töö eelneva arutluskäiguga;
- kasutab akadeemilisi ja mitte-akadeemilisi allikaid;
- vormistab töö korrektselt s.h. kasutab nii stiililiselt kui grammatiliselt korrektset keelt, vormistada viited ning kasutatud allikad järgides ühtset stiili ning akadeemilise viitamise tavasid;
- oskab selgitada ja kaitsta oma uurimistöö tulemusi akadeemilises diskussioonis ning vastata uurimistööga seotud küsimustele.

description.et:
The MA thesis is assessed upon to the following:

* the topicality of the research;
* the thesis' engagement with the topic in question;
* the set aims (their clarity, realistic considerations etc.) and research tasks (whether carrying these out brings the goal closer or not);
* the thesis structure (coherence, balance, consistency etc.);
* the level of analysis and comprehensiveness of material (clarity, relevance, thoroughness, correctness and logicality of analysis, validity of conclusions, material combination skills, adequateness and sufficiency of material etc.);
* the sufficiency, topicality and level of sources (e.g. evaluating between topical articles in an internationally renowned publication or a few newspaper articles);
* referencing (if all facts and principal standpoints (claims, descriptions of links etc.) are verifiable from original sources);
* the linguistic correctness of the thesis;
* the thesis' accordance to the formatting requirements
* the accomplishment of set tasks and goals;
* the student's own argumentation skills.
The assessment is differentiated and follows the assessment standard scale of the University of Tartu ("excellent" - A, "very good" - B, "good" - C, "satisfactory" - D, "poor" - E, "fail" - F).

grade_evaluation.et:
When grading the MA thesis, the committee will take into account the following:

* Thesis content and formatting;
* The MA student's presentation at the defense (the content and its presentation, answering questions posed etc.);
* The opponents review and supervisor's opinion.

After the defense of the MA thesis the committee will decide in a closed discussion if the degree applicant will be awarded an MA in International Relations and Regional Studies and a grade reflective of the quality of analysis within a given topic. The opponent's and supervisor's opinion will not bind the decision of the committee, but is taken into consideration.
